<h4>7. Shuiwan Road, Zhuhai</h4>
<p>A street full of bars. It seems that each one is dedicated to making the loudest music possible to drown out their competition next door. Not a place for quiet conversation. A lively place especially at weekends.</p>
<h4>8. Shenzhen Airport</h4>
<p>A modern wonder, with the most dazzling ceiling which seems to go on forever. If this is what contemporary Chinese architecture can produce, I’m a fan. This airport get the award for best transition to modern times and very rightfully too. What a design &#8211; simply fantastic. This is beautiful architecture, an ultra modern design that is light and airy. Services and facilities are first rate. It&#8217;s probably the nicest airport in China. Good signage and easy to navigate without a translator. Strongly recommended to go through this Airport to see what the Chinese can do to an airport. Simply brilliant.</p>
